	Great place again	Stayed at Carriage House for 1 week from Halloween 09. We returned to this hotel again after 1st visiting in 2005 and were impressed by the upgrade the rooms and hotel have received. We booked 2 rooms as our son came with us and both rooms were large and comfortable. Reception area has also been renovated with good quality furnishings. Staff are very helpful and courteous. Visited Utah and Death Valley whilst staying this time, both an easy day trip. There is a lot of building work being carried out on the strip between the Monte Carlo and Bellagio hotel (which is not far from the Carriage House) this makes the area dusty. Also the entrance to Harmon Avenue from the strip is being changed, this isn't too much of a problem but something you should be aware of if driving in Vegas. Vegas is a fun city with plenty to do, the Carriage House is a 5 minute walk from the strip and gives a welcome bit of peace and quiet when you turn in for the night. The hotel could benefit from a small bar or restaurant but with the strip so close it's not an essential addition the management should make. We would definetly stay at the Carriage House again if we retuned to Las Vegas.	
