Nov 20 2008 	Carriage House - EXCELLENT!	My wife and I just returned from Las Vegas after spending a week at the Carriage House (CH). If you're looking for a peaceful getaway from the hussel &amp; bussel of Vegas, CH is it!! While we love Vegas, it can get annoying having to navigate around some of the more popular hotels. CH is a breath of fresh air. We traded our timeshare for a 2 bedroom/2 bath unit at CH and were very pleased. As other writers have noted, there is construction in the area, so if this is a concern, request a higher numbered room. The lower numbers are on the end of the building near the PH construction. We were in 301 and the noise never bothered us - even with the windows open.And yes - there is no restaurant or bar on premise, but again, it's nice to escape the traffic. The Staff is excellent, very accommodating and even printed our boarding passes. Security is excellent and we never felt uncomfortable walking the 2 blocks to the strip.If you don't mind the slight walk (one trick is to enter the PH side entrance - this cuts off a lot of walking in traffic and construction) to get to the strip, then CH is a gem in the forest of mega-resorts.Many THANKS to CH and Staff for a great, peaceful vacation! We'll be back!!L&amp;J	
