Sep 25 2008 	Great Clean Comfortable Hotel!	My husband and I stayed here for 3 nights while I attended a work conference and were VERY pleased with our stay. The hotel is a short drive from the airport (less than 10 minutes) and a very short walk to the strip (1 block). The hotel is right next to Planet Hollywood and almost &quot;center strip&quot; in my opinion (although it is a long walk all the way up to the north end of the strip). The hotel lobby was under construction when we were there, but even so was still clean and well kept. Security in the hotel was also very good as you need a keycard to get in to the hotel after 10pm and you must have a keycard to use the elevator. When we arrived we were told that they did not have a non-smoking deluxe suite available (I guess I had failed to request a non-smoking room). I told them that we had to have a non-smoking room (the problem was we were leaving on a Saturday and the system would not let them give us a room as they were booked for the weekend). So he talked with the manager and we were upgraded to a one bedroom suite at no extra charge - wow! What a room and what a deal! My husband and decided after seeing the room that we would definitely choose that hotel and a one room suite if we ever go back to Vegas with kids in tow. The room was huge! There was a full kitchen (fridge, dishwasher, freezer, sink, microwave, coffeemaker, stove - no oven though), a living room with sofa and TV and pull down sleeper bed, and a bedroom with a king size bed, TV, and walk in closet. The room was truly HUGE. The bathroom had a sink inside and a second vanity in the bedroom. Everything was clean and well kept. I'm easily disgusted by hotel rooms and I felt very comfortable here. There is no wi-fi like the website advertises, but there is a high speed DSL connection that you can connect to in room - bring your own cable though. The grocery store is not within walking distance, but would probably just be a short drive or taxi ride 