Dec 8 2006 	A great place for longer stays	We stayed at the Carriage House for 7 nights in November 06 as part of a 2 week vacation in Las Vegas. The first week we stayed at a casino/gaming hotel (see my review about the Orleans Hotel &amp; Casino) and upon our return from a trip to the Grand Canyon, we checked into the Carriage House. The staff were very friendly and even remembered that it was our wedding anniversary (I had mentioned it when I did the booking). We had booked a suite, and it was absolutely wonderful. There was a box of chocolates awaiting us on the dining table with a card which we thought was a very nice touch. The sitting-room area was really huge, with a big comfy sofa and large coffee table. There were 2 tv sets in the suite, one in the bedroom and one in the sitting-room area. The bedroom has a king size bed with good quality linen and spare bedding in the large closet. There was also an ironing board, iron and vacuum cleaner! There is a round dining table with 4 chairs, a breakfast bar with 2 stools and a fully equipped kitchen with full size oven, electric hob, dish washer, microwave, fridge and coffee maker. All the cutlery and crockery were spotless, and the frying pans, pots, bowls etc were reasonably new and in very good condition. They supplied us with dishwasher powder and washing-up liquid, tea towels etc. The only fault I could find with the suite is that the bathroom was small compared to other places we had stayed at, and there was no bath but a large walk-in shower instead. We weren't planning on spending more time than we had to in the bathroom anyway, so it wasn't that much of any issue. There is a pool and hot tub situated just across from the lobby and you need to use your room key to access the pool area which means nobody can just wander in from off the street.The pool was heated so we were able to use it even though the pool area was shaded for the large part of the day. There is also a tennis court, and although we did not use it personally, we did see some couples enjoying a couple of sets. The Carriage House is within easy walking distance of the Desert Passage at the Aladdin, where there are loads of shops and places to eat. A few more minutes walk takes you to the Strip and for those wishing to buy show tickets, it is advisable to get to the large Coca-Cola shaped ticketing booth around 10.15am. The shutters open at 11am but you will find that lines start forming very early. There is currently building work going on EVERYWHERE in and around Vegas, I have never seem so much construction work happening at the same time. This also means a lot of dust, heavy traffic and congestion in certain areas. There are also two large construction sites adjacent to the Carriage House and the workers start very early in the morning. If you are a light sleeper you may be disturbed by the noise, so much so that you can ask for a free pair of ear plugs at the reception desk. I did find, however, that after the 3rd night I got accustomed to the noise and it did not bother me that much after then. Otherwise there is really nothing to find fault with in this hotel. There is a laundry room with coin operated washers and dryers, and there is an internet access terminal in the lobby if you do not have your own laptop/notebook to connect in the room. I have no hesitation in recommending it to anyone who does not wish to stay in a busy, smoky, gaming hotel. If you're travelling with kids and want a more relaxing, quiet environment then this is the place for you. I will most definetely stay there again next time we head to Vegas.	
Nov 26 2006 	A nice respite from the hectic strip	There is a lot going on in Vegas so you will find Carriage Housea nice break from the action. The facility is clean. Staff very hospitable. There is a tennis/basketball court, fenced pool and internet access, concierge service, vending machines, parking on site. It is conveniently walkable to Aladdin and the Passage Mall. Plenty of venues for dining, convenience/quick markets within mall and on strip on block to the North. Other hotels are within reach as well. There are no gaming machines but you'll find them all nearby. The rates are very reasonable. You have a refrigerator, microwave and stove top to save you money and convenience to throw something quick together if you don't want to go out to eat.There are a number of construction projects within Las Vegas that may cause some inconvenience not just to this hotel but a number of others in the area. You'll find this property a good value.	
