May 4 2006	Great stay but where did Joey's Bistro Go!	I had read previous reviews of this hotel and decided to stay there due to its location along the strip. I arrived to the hotel early around 10am and the guest services clerks for the hotel where excellent and friendly. They were able to get us a room early and the room was very nice. The room faced the new construction being built but i was not bothered by it as i could barely hear the noise with the windows closed. The pool was also very nice and well kept. I arrived the weekend of the 28th of April. The hotel is a block away from the strip and the walk is a short one to the strip next to the Aladdin Hotel. I would recommend eating at the Harley Davidson resturant if you get the chance as the food was reasonably priced and very good. I was disappointed to see a sign in the hotel that stated Joeys Bistro was closed indefinately. I wished i had known that prior to booking the hotel since there is nowhere to eat in the hotel. I would of liked at least a continental breakfast at the hotel since the Bistro is not open now. I would stay at this hotel again as i enjoyed my stay and would recommend it to others.	
Apr 28 2006	First impressions can be wrong!	Our first impression of the Carriage House was not good. Its at least twenty years since I last drove in Las Vegas and it took over an hour to drive the couple of miles from the Airport- managing to miss the Carriage House by a block on at least three attempts. At the moment the hotel is surrounded by large building sites so the first impression is not good.Happily this impression was wrong,once inside, the building work is not a problem. We had a suite on the top floor that just been renovated - all brand new furniture and fittings. The staff are friendly and very helpful. The Carriage House is very well situated only about 100 metres from the entrance to the Passage Mall under the Alladdin and easy walking to most strip attractions,its also nice to be a little way from the crowds on the strip. If you need a Taxi go into the underground parking area under the Alladdin there is a taxi rank there. Taxis dont seem to like coming to the hotels so its better to go out and find one.We will certainly stay at the Carriage House again when we are in Las Vegas.	
Apr 22 2006	Great location and friendly staff.	Overall we really liked the Carriage House Hotel. It was an oasis from the casinos, only one block from the strip and easy to find, right behind the Aladdin.One issue we had was that I'd spoken to the reservation agent by phone who said that their large suite with the two pull outs would be most suitable for our two children. I said I'd book it online later which I did. However, when we arrived, the room was pretty small especially with the sofa bed pulled out. It was past midnight but I spoke to the person on the front desk who offered me a rollaway. The next day it transpired that the large rooms aren't allocated to those that book online. I shall remember for next time. It was never mentioned by the reservationist.The suite overall was fine and the kitchen area large, clean and well equiped and would have been great if we had been there longer. The bathroom was very small with only a shower, no tub. The goodies included shampoo, lotion and soap though I picked up a shower hat from reception. The pool is across from the car parking though from the photos it looks much closer. There is some construction work going on nearby but we didn't hear it. The restaurant is apparently closed right now though of course there are a million other places to eat. I would definitely stay here again if I could get one of the bigger rooms so we didn't feel so cramped. The staff were all very friendly and helpful.	
