Nov 18 2005	Overall a good hotel	My husband and I stayed at the Carriage House for our honeymoon from October 15 to October 22. Our first impression was that the studio room was beautiful. The king sized bed was comfortable and the decor was excellent. No flower drapes or bedspreads in sight. The kitchen was well-equipt.The strip was definately in walking distance, 5-10 minute walk, but found that there was much more action at the other side of the strip, so we tended to park our rented vehicle at a hotel and then tour the closest ones each day (parking is free at all hotels).Problem with the hotel? There were a few. First, housekeeping is definately lacking. Hairs were left in tub and on sink numerous days. Carpet needed a good shampoo, and I don't believe it was vacuumed more than twice for the week we were there. I spilt some pop on the sheets day 3 and they weren't changed until day 5. Second, though most of the staff where very nice, one night we decided that we would like to rent a movie so we called the front desk. The lady told us that we decided to not have access to movies when we checked in. When we told her no one meantioned movies to us, she basically said that we were lying because it was right in her computer. (why would we do this?). Anyways, we thought it would be pretty easy to flick a switch, but I guess not, since she rudely told us to turn the tv off and wait a few minutes. We did this, the movie didn't come up, and we gave up, rather than call her back and deal with her. Thirdly, the pool really lacked cleanliness, used towels were constantly piled to the brim of the bin, ash trays not emptied, etc.Construction seemed to be a problem for some guests but not us, since we were on the other side of the building.The nicest thing about this hotel was the lack of casino and the fact that you didn't have to walk miles to your room. It was very quiet and we did not hear any noices, people, etc. in the hallways late at night or anything like that.Overall, a good hotel if your looking for a cheaper stay in Vegas, but don't expect anything glamerous.	
Nov 15 2005	Fantastic!!	Stayed at this fantastic hotel with my husband in november 2005 for 5 nights. Had a one bedroom suit which was brilliant, very spacious complete with TV in lounge and bedroom, 6 seater dining table, fully functioning kitchen (fridge freezer, dishwasher, cooker, toaster, coffee maker, kettle). The rooms were very clean and well furnished as was the hotel in general.The staff were very friendly and helpful and check in took minutes as we were the only guests checking in at the time. This was great as during our stay we witnessed check in queues at other hotels which were miles long!The hotel is minutes from the strip and a great location. The construction work around the hotel is still ongoing but we were on the other side of the hotel so we never heard a thing. It is worth requesting a quiet room when booking. There is construction work going on all over Vegas so hard to avoid really.The hotel had no casino which suited us. Walk into the lobby and straight into the lift, no having to walk miles through a casino to the room.I have stayed in strip hotels previously and can honestly say &quot;never again&quot;. The carriage house offers a fantastic little hotel in a great location for less than the strip hotels, most of which are no were near the standard of the carriage house!Lastly i couldn't leave without a mention for Joey's bistro in the hotel. It tends to close around 9 if not busy and most diners seem to go for dinner then head out so its busy earlier on and well worth booking a table at. Superb! We dined there twice in our 5 night stay. On one visit we met a couple who live in vegas who were regulars and knew the waitresses by name. So if the locals dine there its good enough for me. The whole experience at the carriage house was faultless and i would recommend to anyone.	
