Nov 10 2005	A liittle Oasis - and great for kids!	My wife and our two children stayed in one of the bedroom family suites at the Carriage House for six nights in October 2005. There was easily enough room for the four of us and the facilities were excellent; microwave, cooker, fridge, coffee maker, dishwasher (very important!) etc. with dishwasher liquid and coffee re-filled each day. Both the bedroom and the living room (where the kids slept on a large sofa bed) had TV’s, meaning we didn’t have to watch Sponge Bob all the time.We were on the second floor directly facing the construction site at the rear. Ear plugs made a big difference, but it was still possible to hear the beeping of the forklift trucks early in the morning – I couldn’t hear anything else though, not even the kids! However, it must be said the construction of the extension to the MGM is very much ongoing. One building was nearing completion, whilst another was only just beginning, with the piled foundations about half complete (poured concrete, so no pile-drivers) but probably another 9-12 months to go until full completion (my wife gave me a hard time for taking an interest, being a civil engineer!!).The staff are very professional and friendly and were always on hand to help. There was never more than one or two people being served at reception at any time, but always two staff on duty, meaning you never had to wait long to be seen. We arrived at 5.30pm on a Saturday and check-in took less than 10mins. We needed a car for a couple of days, so the staff arranged one through Budget (they actually pick you up at the hotel and take you to their depot 10mins away) which was $20 dollars cheaper than the same quoted by the Budget counter around the corner on the Strip and we also saved on the higher airport tax! Being a family with kids (11 and 8) meant we couldn’t enjoy all the slot machines and gambling (one of the reasons for choosing the Carriage House, since we didn’t want to walk though acres of machines to get to our room). What we liked as a family was the Desert Passage at the Aladdin, with its shops and family friendly restaurants, which really is, less than five minutes walk away.The kids liked the swimming pool which was never too busy. The pool is across the hotel access road (very quiet) in front of reception, but you need your room key to get in, so is quite safe. Also, next to the pool is the tennis court, which the kids really loved (they have smaller racquets if required) Since it's elevated, they managed to lose all their tennis balls, but the staff didn’t seem to mind – they probably enjoy going into the swimming pool to retrieve them!Other things we liked about the Carriage House; laundry on every floor with washing machines and driers (essential for families or those with few clothes); internet access ($5 for 20mins or $10 for 50min) – We used it every day with 10mins being the longest wait; Joeys Bar – it was busy with a wedding taking place when we visited, but afterwards was quiet enough for everyone to get a window seat for the great view. Kids meals were good value at $3.99 and we enjoyed ours, especially with a bottle of house wine (a good accompaniment to the ear plugs!!).All in all, a little oasis amongst the madness.	
