Oct 10 2005	Great Hotel Noisy construction	My wife and I stayed at this hotel for a week from Oct 1-8th. We had a spacious and clean one bedroom suite w/ a kitchenette. The staff was very helpful and kind in taking care of us and answering our questions. The only downside to this hotel was the construction on both sides of the building. We were on the third story on the east side of the building. There is condo/high rise going up across the street from us and it was very noisy. Truck would arrive in the middle of the night and you would hear the forklifts beeping as they unloaded the supplies from the truck. Also, the Pile Drivers at 6:00am were a nice wakeup call. The hotel did offer earplugs and noise machines to help drown out the construction noise. We did know about the construction prior to going down there, so it wasn't a surprise, but it was just louder than we expected. Ask for a room on the inside of the hallway and it will be a lot quieter. Also, the monorail is only a five minute walk down to the MGM Grand. All in all, great hotel, just on the noisy side. Don't expect a lot of sleep. Then again, it is Vegas.	
