Aug 29 2005	Close enough to the strip yet far enough away	Stayed in this hotel 1st week of August 2005. Situated not on the strip but only minutes walk to the Aladdin Passageway, which has shops and restaurants, and takes you through to The Aladdin Hotel and Casino.There is a lot of construction being carried out around the surrounding area but we were only woken up once in the night/early morning.Went to the restaurant on the top floor with some sights of the hotels on the strip, food was lovely with friendly staff.The hotel staff assisted us with all our queries including finding us the telephone number to book a trip to Alcatraz when we moved on to San Francisco.Rooms were quite big, and very comfortable, would have liked 2 bathrooms as there was 4 of us but we managed.Our only complaint was the air condititioning, it worked fine on the 1st day but then decided to pack up, when we complained to the reception they said it had frozen and to leave it off for a couple of hours. When we switched it back on it still didn't work so we informed reception again, and within minutes they sent a maintenance person to our room. He worked on the air conditioning for at least half an hour and replaced a part. It did work after this but not as good as other air conditioning we have experienced, with temperatures above 100 degrees it was uncomfortable to say the least.All in all I would recommend The Carriage Hotel and will definetly stay there again.	
Aug 5 2005	Not on the Strip but close enough to walk	This hotel was generally nice, but there were a few problems. There was a tobacco odor in the hallway and in our room, which was non-smoking. However, it's probably hard not to have a smell of tobacco anywhere in Las Vegas. Also, we were woken up by some machinery making loud sounds at 3:45 A.M. There's a huge hotel tower being built next door, and the staff of the Carriage House told us that the construction often happens at night. Despite these problems, the room was comfortable, and the Strip is within easy walking distance. Other advantages were the safe provided in the room and the two elevators, which seemed unnecessary for a hotel of its size.	
Aug 3 2005	You don't have to be the biggest to be the best	We stayed at The Carriage House as part of a Timeshare exchange. There were 7 of us including 3 children so we took a 2 bedroomed apartment.The apartment was very spacious, well decorated, well set out and with everything we could have wanted. The kids could play or watch TV in their own bedroom so never got under our feet.It was cleaned every day and the cleaners were very friendly and efficient, always ready for a chat and made our stay very easy indeed.Booking in was simple and quick, no queues and the reception staff were always excellent.Joey's restaurant on the top floor offered good food at a good price whether you ate in or took a take out.The hotel does not have any gaming facilities which was fine by us with having 3 children, besides the strip is only 200 yards away.There is building work going on outside as the MGM which is next to The Carriage House is extending even further, this work starts early and finishes late so outside it can get dusty and the road is busy with site traffic. However the noise created was minimal and not enough to spoil our stay.There is re-furbishment of a few rooms going on inside the Carriage House as well but again it did not affect any part of our stay.There is a pool outside the main entrance which is small but large enough to sunbathe and swim and play in.All in all, we enjoyed The Carriage House, the staff make the hotel and we would recommend it to any family which includes young children or teenages who are looking to stay somehere away from the hustle and bustle of the main areas of Ls Vegas.	
Jul 21 2005	Fine hotel for the price	I stayed in the Carriage House for three nights last April, and overall I was satisfied. The room was spacious and in good shape and the staff quite friendly. The strip, which is where a lot of casinos are located, is a ten-minute walk away.The hotel has few amenities: there is a restaurant on the top floor (beware of being assigned a room right underneath -- it can be very loud), a very small pool out by the parking lot, and a little lounge off the lobby. There was no Internet connection in the rooms when I visited (I was told that it would be installed), and two *huge* buildings were being constructed on two sides of the hotel (I did not find the noise bothersome). I would ask about the construction when making reservations.	
Jul 6 2005	Large rooms kitchen and room layout nice good price...	Stayed here for our honeymoon. The rooms are large, we saved alot having our own kitchen and having lunch and dinner inside. Location is great, close to Paris, MGM, and many other hotels on the strip. With the money saved in this hotel, use the extra money for a day pass on the bus, you can get more of your vacation if you can do that. The pool was great. There is also a shuttle service, but is around for a few trips a day. The activities are great as well and the hotel staff are very helpful. I would come back to this hotel for sure.	
Jun 29 2005	Great value and well located	This is a non-gambling hotel which we specifically wanted. My girlfriend and I stayed here for 5 nights in the first week of March 05. We paid US$89/night except for Saturday night which was US$109.The hotel was clean, modern with friendly staff. Our room was big (compared to UK hotel rooms) and more than enough for the two of us. As the hotel is self-catering only, a cooker, fridge/freezer, cutlery, etc. were provided free of charge. The room was well cleaned every day. A bus is put on each a couple of times a week to drive guests to the local Vons supermarket (10 or so minute drive each way). The clean, warm pool is situated opposite the hotel (as shown on their web site) and is accessed though key card. The hotel is within 10 minute walk of The Strip (no more than 15 minutes for slow walkers).There was a laundry room on our floor (and I guess all floors) with a large washing machine and a separate dryer machine which were both cheap to use. From memory, about US$2 each.The weather was hot during our stay and so we had our window open. Due to the building work going on nearby, we heard building site machinery start up around 7am. This wasn't a big issue though so don't let it put you off.Also, there's an Internet terminal in the foyer which is expensive compared to UK prices and doesn't have the quickest connection speed!Overall, a great hotel with good value for money and one which we would definitely return too.Point of interest:When you arrive at the airport there are various mini-vans positioned outside the airport which drop customers off at designated hotels around/on The Strip. We paid our driver up front - he then disappered for 40 minutes before returning and dropping us and the other passengers at our respective hotels - very frustrating. It is far quicker - and cheaper by a few $ - to hire a taxi. The journey takes no more than 15 minutes as the Carriage House is approx. 3 miles from the airport.	
