May 21 2005	Great family escape but blighted by nearby construction work	A reasonably priced non-gaming hotel with kitchens, a block and a half off Strip. The Carriage House has helpful, friendly staff and a quality Italian restaurant (Joeys), at roof level with great views over the Strip.Sadly the hotel is currently blighted by some major adjacent construction. Pile drivers gave us all a rude awakening at 6am on our first morning there. However, staff responded positively to our request to change to a room on the other side of the hotel, and gave us a good choice of alternatives.Our second room overlooked the pool, and was much larger and more suitable for the 4 adults in our party. Construction on this side of the building was also much quieter. The kitchen was very well equipped, making this hotel a great choice for families, and there are useful laundry rooms too.Small hotels in Vegas mean you escape the check in/taxi queues encountered in large resort hotels, but bear in mind that pools and other facilities are naturally more basic as a result.We'd use The Carriage House again - but only when all the neighbouring construction work is finished.	
