e!!	
Oct 26 2004	Absolutely Superb!	My wife and I stayed at the Carriage House for a week from 16 – 23 October. We had both been to Vegas before and didn’t really want to stay in another casino hotel with the usual five mile walk to and from our room, so we booked the Carriage House after reading the reviews on this site. We were not disappointed. The location, accommodation and the staff are all superb. For about the same cost as a standard room in some of the bigger Strip hotels, we got a huge corner suite comprising an ample kitchenette (microwave, hob, big fridge/freezer, dishwasher etc), large bedroom with king size bed, walk in closet with plenty of hanging and drawer space, in room safe, iron &amp; ironing board and hairdryer. The bathroom was a bit on the small side compared to other Vegas hotel bathrooms but as there was a separate vanity unit and washbasin in the bedroom, there was never any fights to get near a mirror!Just before we arrived, the hotel informed me that the courtesy airport pick-up was no longer available. However, they added that we should simply get a cab and they would reimburse the cost which was a very nice touch. They also arranged courtesy drop off at the airport and also provided courtesy transport to and from a local grocery store (complete with discount cards) so we could stock up on the essentials for a week in Vegas (OJ, beer and Cheetos)!There is a hot tub and a pool which is a bit small but as we never used it, it didn’t make any difference to us. We had a couple of drinks in Joey’s bar on the top floor (Carriage House guests get a discount) which has nice views of the strip. The hotel is a (safe) five minute walk from the strip and just across the street from the side entrance to the Aladdin Desert Passage. While the front desk will call a cab for you, if you are in a hurry my tip would be to get one at the taxi/valet area at the Aladdin.If I am ever back in Vegas, I would have no hesitation in staying again at the Carriage House.	
Sep 16 2004	Better than expected!	My husband and I stayed at the Carriage house hotel in a 1 bedroom suite for a week (Aug 28th). We arrived late (flight was late, missed connecting flight, had to take two other connecting flights instead - I hate flying), but staff were very helpful. Our luggage visited Chicago before finally deciding to join us at our hotel at 3am - front desk called to let us know it arrived as requested (&quot;are you sure?&quot;).Suite was cleaned daily but they don't do dishes - but it's not like I cooked on holiday! I think a bowl of cereal was as adventurous as we got. Full kitchen was helpful - kept all our beer and water cold.Location of the hotel was good. View was bad - construction of the MGM residences going on behind (our view), construction of the Marriott timeshire in front. But the hotel was more or less accross from the Desert Passage at the Aladdin - easy access to big margaritas at La Salsa. Also next to the MGM from the back - but it's a long walk when it's over 100 degrees in the shade and you have a big blister on your foot. Room was right in level with the Monorail - it actually worked the first few days we were there, but we didn't hear it. Got to ride it once - too bad we bought a family ticket that we never got to use the remainder (2/3) of the trips!Hotel had decent cable TV and had free HBO. They also provide shuttle serve to/from airport and to the grocery stores free of charge (but has to be pre-booked). There is a restaurant upstairs that is supposed to be good, but we never tried as we were never in the mood for Italian food while we were there.Would definately consider staying there again.	
Jul 15 2004	Great time at The Carriage House	Stayed at The Carriage House from June 10-15, 2004. Had a wonderful time without the kids for the couple days!! Staff was great and facility was well maintained from housekeeping to maintaining the towels at the pool. A minor note...the pool was bit to small for the the people using it... especially since there were several families with multiple children. There was no where to go inside of the pool to avoid the diving and splashing from the kids..(This not deserving to take away the perfect rating of The Carriage House) Would not hesitate to return!!	
Jul 6 2004	A great place to stay	We stayed at the Carriage House at the end of June. The place was wonderful. Although my wife missed having a casino in the lobby the proximity of the Aladdin and MGM kept her happy. I think the place should be rated higher than the 3 stars it gets in most sites. The cleanliness, amenities, thickness of the towels in the room and at the pool seemed to place the hotel higher in my ratings. The desk and housekeeping staff were friendly and took care of every need quickly. Joey's Bistro Restaurant on the top floor was excellent, with great food at reasonable prices. We had a master suite with a separate bedroom with a king sized bed and full kitchen. The pool was never overcrowded as it was at every other Vegas resort we've been to. We will definitely go to the Carriage house again.	
May 5 2004	A week in Vegas	My wife and I stayed for a week in Vegas 4/24-5/1, 2004. We had a timeshare exchange at the Carriage House. It was a great place to spend a week as it really was our 'home away from home'. It was a one bedroom unit which could sleep up to six people, though I think that would have been 2 too many unless they were your children. We had a full kitchen in which we prepared many of our meals. It was clean and located about 1 1/2 blocks off the southern end of the strip ( across the street from the entrance to Aladdin's Desert Passage shopping area). It had a nice pool and generally was quite a pleasant place to stay. It was very quiet and we always looked forward to ending our busy days (or nights) there as a refuge from the hustle and bustle of Las Vegas in general and the strip in particular. Though we thorougly enjoyed seeing all of the lights and shows of the hotels along the strip, we liked being able to get away from it at the Carriage House when we grew weary.Las Vegas is noted for the gambling, casinos and neon and all of this is very exciting. However, not to be missed is the Valley of Fire State Park which is an hour northeast of the city. It has spectacular, otherworldly rock formations. Quite a contrast to the city lights and glitz. Another location even closer to the strip but worlds away would be the Red Rock conservation area located about 20 miles west of Las Vegas. It also provides some terrific natural beauty. Las Vegas also had some interesting museums which are worth a trip if you have time. We visited the Natural History museum which has exhibits featuring dinosaurs, african creatures, Nevada wildlife and world wildlife. Located next to this museum is the Mormon Pioneer Park. This location is being restored to what is was the mid 19th century when the Mormons first settled here. Slowly but surely this site is being restored with reconstruction of the old mormon fort. A couple of walls now stand with more on the way. Another museum we visited was the Nevada State Museum &amp; Historical Society in Lorenzi Park. This museum had displays about the regional history of this area along with some earth and bilogical science exhibits. At the time we visited there was an exhibit of some of the old and now retired Vegas neon signs from earlier era's. This was my first trip which I stayed in Vegas for any length of time. I was amazed by all of the mega resorts and the different themes for each one. My own take on this experience is that Las Vegas is like a Disneyland for adults with each of the resort/casinos being there own 'land'. We had a terrific time.	
Apr 10 2004	Carriage house just right	My wife and I stayed at the Carriage House during Spring Break March 04. I had called to confirm our reservations and happen to mention that it was for our 25th wedding aniversity. When we got to our room they had a box of chocolates there. The room was simple and quiet. Perfect for sleep and a quick shower before a show, and a great price. We spent most of our money eating at great resturants and shows. Thanks Carriage house.	
Apr 5 2004	Great Stay at the Carriage House	Just got back from Vegas and stayed a week at the Carrriage House. There were four of us and we shared one of the two bedroom two bathroom rooms and it was very roomy and comfortable. The location is very convenient to the Aladdin and MGM. We were able to walk almost anywhere on the strip and also the front desk was great about calling cabs for us. Although the front desk personnel could have been nicer, our stay was very pleasant. However, the best part of the Carriage House is the great Joey Bistro on the top floor. They have a great Italian menu and a great happy hour. Greg, the bartendar was the best! We were probably some of the youngest people there and we are in our early 30's.	
