Feb 1 2004	Loved the Carriage House	Just returned from a Christmas &amp; New Years stay at the Carriage House. We loved it. Quick check in. Beautiful full sized 1 bedroom apartment. We could have moved in. Love the fact that it is so quiet with no casino &amp; peaceful &amp; tasteful lobby when you return from the craziness of the strip. The restaurant( Joey Bistro) on the roof was very good. Bobbi is a kick &amp; will help with any tickets you might need. Definitely will return.	
Jan 21 2004	Best Value on the Strip	Recently stayed at the Carriage House (1/16/04) for two nights and it was terrific. It is only a half block from the side entrance to Aladdin. We drove into the free parking lot, parked right in front, walked in and immediately got service at the reception desk. No long lines of people, no jangling slot machines, no long trip through hallways and hallways and elevators to our room.In fact, they upgraded us to a complimentary suite, no charge - I guess they had room. We had a huge kitchen, den, bedroom and bath with big walk in shower. Within ten minutes we were unpacked and ready to go explore. Rate was comparable to a seedy hotel directly on the Strip and tons less than a Bellagio or Aladdin. They have a small bar and restaurant on the top floor. Good views of the Strip, immediate service - you can have a drink before bed and even take the glass to your room. They also have numerous vending machines in the lobby with a wide variety of choices, and free coffee in a nearby conference room. (We had a coffeepot in our room, too.) We didn't try the restaurant but it looked good. They even left us a comprehensive list of free things to do in Vegas, including times and directions.I will definitely stay here again and recommend to my friends. It was a bargain and a pleasure. Even though I had researched it on the Internet before going, it surpassed my expectations. Good job, Carriage House!	
Nov 17 2003	A time Share Days' Inn	We did not actually stay here, but took a timeshare sales pitch for the place. While this may disqualify this review for posting, I thought it important to let folks know that this hotel is also a timeshare. (No, we did not buy.)The facilities, however, were nice enough, though not elegant or fancy by any means. Qualatatively, they deserve about three stars (plus) out of five, and seem comparable to something one would get at a Hawthorn Suites. It is not, however, as good as an Embassy Suites or a Hyatt Hotel.	
